oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Unifrom of an unidentified soldier from Wilson County, Tennessee
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: A khaki cotton drill uniform consisting of tunic and breeches. The tunic has enlisted collar discs, "U.S." on the right and medical corps on the left. An Advanced Sector of Supply shoulder patch is loosely attached on the left sleeve and a service chevron is on the forearm. The breeches are of standard pattern with lacing. The Advanced Sector of Supply was a composite unit of support organizations and could include medical, quartermaster, commissary, transportation, and ordnance personnel.
